{
  "texts": [
    "Consistent with prior work 38, 41, however, we also observe potential tensions between different rules specified by the participants, in both scope and specificity (e.g.",
    "when being harmless means potentially being less helpful).",
    "While these tensions exemplify greater coverage, they require further prioritisation efforts to create a clearer understanding of when it is appropriate for some rules to take precedence over others.",
    "This is especially important as this approach is scaled, since different groups might foreground different issues or even have incompatible preferences.",
    "Resolving these conflicts might require either further engagement with relevant communities or deference to other stakeholders, or both, to help with prioritisation. 5."
  ]
}